<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-267-162 </DOCNO><DOCID>08 462 628</DOCID><JOURNAL>Soft-Letter  May 7 1990 v7 n20 p6(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT The Mercury Group 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Borland. (Borland International Inc VP Spencer Leyton's anecdoteabout Lotus 1-2-3)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT/><TEXT>BORLAND BORLAND vice president Spencer Leyton on Lotus's strategy of creatingversions of 1-2-3 for many different platforms: &quot;The Eskimos have 26 wordsfor snow, which is as important to them as 1-2-3 is to Lotus.andP;  So Lotus willhave versions of white snow, really white snow, really cold white snow, andreally cold damp white snow.&quot;andP;  (Quoted in InfoWorld, 2/12/90)</TEXT></DOC>